1
00:00:01,359 --> 00:00:04,800
If a man or a woman spends
their whole life pleasing others,

2
00:00:04,840 --> 00:00:06,640
then they're not living at all.

3
00:00:06,680 --> 00:00:09,080
It must be very
liberating to think like that.

4
00:00:10,640 --> 00:00:13,600
She is Beowulf's. We
don't choose who we love.

5
00:00:13,640 --> 00:00:16,880
But we can choose who we make
our way through this world with.

6
00:00:16,920 --> 00:00:19,160
They can't take it away
from you now, Rheda.

7
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:21,400
With this marriage, you are Jarl.

8
00:00:21,440 --> 00:00:24,760
Remember, before man
came to the Shieldlands,

9
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:28,600
the only living things
here were the Mudborn.

10
00:00:28,640 --> 00:00:34,200
All with black blood, all born
from this land's dark dirt.

11
00:00:34,240 --> 00:00:37,560
I hear the Warig are causing
your father some concern.

12
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:39,600
He fears they may be rising again.

13
00:00:39,640 --> 00:00:44,360
There's a prophet moving through
the icelands, stirring them up.

14
00:00:44,400 --> 00:00:46,400
The days of peace are over.

15
00:00:46,440 --> 00:00:48,440
This ends here!

16
00:00:48,480 --> 00:00:50,480
(ROARING)

17
00:00:58,680 --> 00:01:00,680
(SCREECHING)

18
00:01:02,920 --> 00:01:05,319
- Yah!
- There! On the left!

19
00:01:05,360 --> 00:01:07,360
Two of them!

20
00:01:07,760 --> 00:01:10,000
- Yah!
- Get them!

21
