22
00:01:26,160 --> 00:01:28,160
(HORSE WHINNIES)

23
00:01:37,480 --> 00:01:39,480
We've lost them.

24
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:48,400
See if you can pick up their tracks.

25
00:01:48,440 --> 00:01:50,440
(SPEAKS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

26
00:01:55,640 --> 00:01:57,640
Good boy.

27
00:01:57,680 --> 00:01:59,680
Scout upstream.

28
00:02:02,360 --> 00:02:05,000
I've never seen
them this close to Herot.

29
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:06,800
(SNARLING)

30
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:09,680
Warig! Help!

31
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:18,840
Behind you!

32
00:02:18,880 --> 00:02:20,880
(GROANS)

33
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:25,400
(THROAT SLITS)

34
00:02:37,080 --> 00:02:39,760
- Help! Please!
- Come on.

35
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:41,800
(YELLING)

36
00:02:44,480 --> 00:02:46,480
(YELLING)

37
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:49,800
(GROANS)

38
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:51,840
(YELLING)

39
00:02:58,680 --> 00:03:00,640
Gil, wait.

40
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:03,600
- Maybe we can question it.
- All right.

41
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:08,480
Your friend... he gave his life for me.

42
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:10,520
They attacked you?

43
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:13,080
I've been their captive for weeks.

44
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:20,800
You'd better come back with us to Herot.

45
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:22,840
Under our protection.

46
00:03:58,174 --> 00:04:03,944
Synced and corrected by VitoSilans
