47
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:08,480
(SINGING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

48
00:04:36,840 --> 00:04:38,840
- Where have you been?
- Washing.

49
00:04:38,880 --> 00:04:40,880
You should try it sometime.

50
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:43,200
I'll have you know I have
a bath every other summer.

51
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:44,920
I believe you.

52
00:04:44,960 --> 00:04:47,200
For that you're gonna have
to go back in the lake.

53
00:04:47,240 --> 00:04:49,240
(SHRIEKS)

54
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:51,280
Put me down or I will cause you pain!

55
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:54,440
You would too.

56
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:58,800
There's no taming you, is there?

57
00:04:58,840 --> 00:05:01,840
- No.
- Then I'll take you as you are.

58
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:07,640
(LAUGHS)

59
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:11,760
You, my friend, don't know who I am.

60
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:13,800
I will.

61
00:05:19,960 --> 00:05:21,960
(DOG BARKS IN DISTANCE)

62
00:05:48,160 --> 00:05:50,160
(CLATTERING AND BANGING OF TOOLS)

63
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:52,200
MAN: Put it over there, will you?

64
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:57,560
Set it down.

65
00:06:00,440 --> 00:06:01,570
Up.

66
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:12,160
I'll be back before dark. Tell
Vishka I'll come see her.

67
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:14,200
All right?

68
00:06:20,440 --> 00:06:22,680
I'm not an expert on fortification,

69
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:25,800
but I imagine you'll need
gates as well as a wall?

70
00:06:25,840 --> 00:06:27,840
I told her not to go alone.

71
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:32,960
She can take care of herself.

72
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:35,760
The men are out patrolling
the forest for a reason.

73
00:06:47,280 --> 00:06:49,280
(WIND WHISTLES)

74
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:55,560
- Kela.
- (GASPS)

75
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:56,992
Sorry.

76
00:06:57,640 --> 00:06:59,098
I didn't mean to intrude.

77
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:02,139
Leave us.

78
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:07,031
This is your chamber.

79
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:10,700
You should sleep here.

80
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:14,840
Your virtue will be quite
safe, I promise.

81
00:07:19,640 --> 00:07:21,640
Are they looking after you?

82
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:26,680
I rise and I'm
dressed, I sit and I'm fed,

83
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:28,760
I'm thirsty and I'm
brought water or wine.

84
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:35,040
Then I sit, I sew, I'm fed
again, I'm dressed and put back to bed.

85
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:38,160
- (LAUGHS)
- I feel like a doll.

86
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:40,640
I could ask Varr to find
some entertainment for you.

87
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:44,920
No. His idea of
entertainment is a lecture.

88
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:48,320
On the economics of the iron trade.

89
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:50,400
He gave me the same one.

90
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:55,458
(LAUGHS)

91
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:20,846
(SNARLS)

92
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:32,486
(BIRD CALLS)

93
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:39,559
(RUNNING WATER)

94
00:08:41,919 --> 00:08:44,399
(ANIMAL CALLS IN DISTANCE)

95
00:08:47,920 --> 00:08:49,960
You promised me you'd take a Huskarla.

96
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:53,400
- Are you telling me off?
- No, I...

97
00:08:54,560 --> 00:08:55,890
Not really. I...

98
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:58,720
You said you were going to a homestead.

99
00:09:00,920 --> 00:09:02,175
Where are you going?

100
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:13,120
What's this for?

101
00:09:14,600 --> 00:09:16,640
The beast you
wounded at the giant ruins.

102
00:09:19,680 --> 00:09:22,880
You're feeding it? It tried to kill you.

103
00:09:22,920 --> 00:09:25,040
- It's a Mudborn!
- It's never harmed me.

104
00:09:27,120 --> 00:09:29,120
You've been here before?

105
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:33,160
All living things, human or otherwise,

106
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:35,480
are tied together, connected.

107
00:09:36,680 --> 00:09:38,680
- Who told you that?
- My father.

108
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:41,960
- Then he was wrong.
- That's what they told him.

109
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:44,200
Right before they hanged
him from an oak tree.

110
00:09:55,160 --> 00:09:57,188
Elvina! Wait!

111
00:09:59,120 --> 00:10:00,281
Elvina!

112
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:04,150
(LOW GROANING)

113
00:10:04,240 --> 00:10:05,687
(PANICKED YELLING)

114
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:09,600
Elvina!

115
00:10:11,880 --> 00:10:13,359
(SNARLING)

116
00:10:20,760 --> 00:10:22,248
- (LEAVES RUSTLE)
- (YELLS)

117
00:10:27,640 --> 00:10:29,640
(MUTTERING)

118
00:10:33,480 --> 00:10:35,480
Why bring us to Hock?

119
00:10:35,520 --> 00:10:37,520
What do they want?

120
00:10:37,560 --> 00:10:39,560
To toy with us.

121
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:41,600
Before they kill us.

122
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:54,600
(GROWLING)

123
00:10:58,560 --> 00:11:00,560
Your father.

124
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:04,440
What happened to him?

125
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:10,640
He was a healer. Taught
me everything I know.

126
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:14,400
He thought everyone
deserved help, even Mudborn.

127
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:17,840
The Banning found out he'd
been tending to some sick Warig.

128
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:20,240
They hanged him for helping them.

129
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:24,150
I'm sorry.

130
00:11:25,320 --> 00:11:27,920
If you'd been there that
day, would you have been sorry?

131
00:11:27,960 --> 00:11:30,200
Or would you have placed
the noose around his neck?

132
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:46,760
I had a wife.

133
00:11:49,920 --> 00:11:51,920
A son.

134
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:57,080
Some slaves escaped from
a neighbouring village

135
00:11:57,120 --> 00:11:59,120
close to where we lived.

136
00:12:00,120 --> 00:12:03,240
They needed men to hunt
them down so I joined them.

137
00:12:03,280 --> 00:12:06,080
But a few got away from us.

138
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:08,120
Circled back.

139
00:12:17,640 --> 00:12:19,640
All that was left was ashes.

140
00:12:20,840 --> 00:12:22,840
(INAUDIBLE)

141
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:33,080
The Banning were
wrong to hang your father.

142
00:12:34,680 --> 00:12:37,760
But he was wrong to ever think we could
live at peace with the Mudborn.

143
00:12:40,280 --> 00:12:42,880
Those slaves were Warig.

144
00:12:46,360 --> 00:12:47,768
(SHOUTING)

145
00:12:51,400 --> 00:12:53,400
(SNARLING)

146
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:55,440
(YELLING)

147
00:13:10,760 --> 00:13:13,384
(HORN BLASTS)

148
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:20,840
MAN: What are they bringing
that thing here for?

149
00:13:20,880 --> 00:13:23,680
Take our fallen brother to be
prepared for his last journey.

150
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:25,720
Keep an eye on the Warig.

151
00:13:26,480 --> 00:13:29,720
- (ANGRY YELLING FROM CROWD)
- MAN: Give it some justice!

152
00:13:29,760 --> 00:13:31,760
Smash his head in!

153
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:34,920
- Send it back!
- WOMAN: Get it out of here!

154
00:13:43,360 --> 00:13:44,805
Get back!

155
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:51,221
(GROWLS)

156
00:14:00,120 --> 00:14:03,840
The black blood that flows
through their veins binds all the Mudborn.

157
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:08,000
(SHOUTS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

158
00:14:08,360 --> 00:14:09,799
(SPITS)

159
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:13,123
(ROARS)

160
00:14:24,480 --> 00:14:26,373
(STRUGGLES LOUDLY)

161
00:14:30,520 --> 00:14:34,520
- (YELLS ANGRILY)
- Get up. Get up!

162
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:37,366
(GROWLS)

163
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:44,640
Where did you find it?

164
00:14:44,680 --> 00:14:46,680
With two others in the
woods to the east.

165
00:14:49,160 --> 00:14:51,160
They killed one of our men.

166
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:57,800
- You. Do you have a name?
- Razzak.

167
00:14:57,840 --> 00:15:01,760
The most well-known of all
spice traders in the Gulf of Aseeia.

168
00:15:01,800 --> 00:15:04,600
Is Aseeia known for its spices?

169
00:15:05,960 --> 00:15:07,960
No. Not really, no.

170
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:10,000
I think I'm the only one.

171
00:15:10,040 --> 00:15:12,040
The Warig held him captive.

172
00:15:12,080 --> 00:15:14,480
For ten days, maybe more.

173
00:15:15,480 --> 00:15:16,866
Have you ever tried to have an

174
00:15:16,891 --> 00:15:18,760
intelligent conversation with a Warig?

175
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:20,800
You speak their language.

176
00:15:20,840 --> 00:15:23,680
Well, I study quickly when
my life's on the line.

177
00:15:25,080 --> 00:15:27,640
Did they talk of a
prophet called Redtongue?

178
00:15:27,680 --> 00:15:29,680
What have you heard of him?

179
00:15:31,480 --> 00:15:35,400
This is my hall. You won't
mind if I ask the questions,

180
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:38,080
Razzak, the only spice trader of Aseeia?

181
00:15:42,840 --> 00:15:47,240
They did speak of a prophet,
yes. A monster among monsters.

182
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:50,400
They said he drinks
red blood from humans.

183
00:15:50,440 --> 00:15:54,800
They also told of a Skinshifter
here in Herot.

184
00:15:56,320 --> 00:15:57,704
(ROARS)

185
00:15:58,360 --> 00:16:00,225
(GROANS)

186
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:02,760
You will help question this Warig?

187
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:05,560
Anything I can do to be of service.

188
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:10,120
Perhaps, then, you can tell me
more of your time as their captive.

189
00:16:10,160 --> 00:16:12,880
That would be my
great pleasure, Rheda...

190
00:16:14,240 --> 00:16:16,240
Thane of Herot.

191
00:16:18,160 --> 00:16:21,243
(WARIG ANGRILY YELLING)

192
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:26,595
Watch him!

193
00:16:27,240 --> 00:16:30,200
- (GROWLS)
- Talk, scum!

194
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:31,659
(SWORD DRAWN)

195
00:16:52,920 --> 00:16:54,920
I have to find Beowulf.

196
00:16:54,960 --> 00:16:56,960
Give the blood money to your mother.

197
00:17:00,640 --> 00:17:03,720
That money was paid in
exchange for your life, Breca.

198
00:17:03,760 --> 00:17:05,760
Give it to me yourself.

199
00:17:27,839 --> 00:17:29,840
(RUMBLE OF THUNDER)

200
00:17:29,880 --> 00:17:31,880
He knows what he did was wrong.

201
00:17:39,640 --> 00:17:41,400
Where's Beowulf?

202
00:17:41,440 --> 00:17:43,440
Should have let me out this morning.

203
00:17:43,480 --> 00:17:46,480
Might not be pleased to see you.

204
00:17:47,680 --> 00:17:50,680
What? He might kill me?

205
00:17:50,720 --> 00:17:54,080
Might. Why take the risk?

206
00:17:55,360 --> 00:17:57,280
I just returned from Bregan.

207
00:17:57,320 --> 00:17:59,320
Abrecan plans to overthrow Rheda.

208
00:17:59,360 --> 00:18:03,200
If Beowulf's not here, I'll
have to tell her myself.

209
00:18:03,240 --> 00:18:06,800
So you're gonna tell
Rheda that her little brother

210
00:18:06,840 --> 00:18:08,840
has betrayed her?

211
00:18:09,920 --> 00:18:11,920
Good luck with that.

212
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:15,960
You know, Gerd, the more I know you,

213
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:20,120
the more I understand why your
wife beats you with that copper pot.

214
00:18:25,280 --> 00:18:27,280
What do you think you're doing?

215
00:18:28,840 --> 00:18:30,840
Just going to talk to Rheda.

216
00:18:32,480 --> 00:18:35,520
Perhaps you'd like me to have someone
bring you something to drink

217
00:18:35,560 --> 00:18:38,880
- while you chat?
- Some wine? Thank you.

218
00:18:38,920 --> 00:18:40,920
Guards.

219
00:18:42,120 --> 00:18:44,760
You're a murderer and a thief.

220
00:18:47,080 --> 00:18:49,080
What are you even doing in Herot?

221
00:18:52,760 --> 00:18:54,760
I have important news.

222
00:18:56,080 --> 00:18:58,560
What is important news in Breca's world?

223
00:18:59,720 --> 00:19:01,920
Are they giving away
free mead at the tavern?

224
00:19:02,920 --> 00:19:05,400
Or have you found another
widow to steal from?

225
00:19:06,480 --> 00:19:09,040
Perhaps you intend to try
your luck with Rheda herself.

226
00:19:09,080 --> 00:19:12,720
Enlighten me, what is
this important news?

227
00:19:14,960 --> 00:19:18,200
I tell her myself or not at all.

228
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:21,800
Not at all, then.

229
00:19:31,080 --> 00:19:33,080
(SNARLING)

230
00:19:33,120 --> 00:19:35,920
Talk, Warig. We can go all day.

231
00:19:46,480 --> 00:19:48,480
What did it say?

232
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:50,520
That you seem a little angry.

233
00:19:50,560 --> 00:19:52,800
- It will tell you nothing.
- Right.

234
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:57,280
Well, I am angry. You
killed one of my best men!

235
00:19:57,320 --> 00:19:59,320
(YELLS)

236
00:20:00,280 --> 00:20:03,240
(SPITS) Dirt-licking Mudborn scum!

237
00:20:03,280 --> 00:20:06,589
(YELLS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

238
00:20:12,080 --> 00:20:14,080
Where's the spice trader?

239
00:20:15,400 --> 00:20:17,440
I thought he was going
to help us question him.

240
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:42,280
This is the
Huskarla killed by the Warig?

241
00:20:44,560 --> 00:20:46,640
It's a tradition that
the Huskarla commander

242
00:20:46,680 --> 00:20:48,680
prepare the bodies of his dead men.

243
00:20:50,520 --> 00:20:52,520
So he never forgets the cost.

244
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:56,400
May I help?

245
00:20:58,720 --> 00:21:00,720
Your help would be welcome.

246
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:10,996
(HORN BLASTS)

247
00:21:15,280 --> 00:21:17,611
Yah! Yah!

248
00:21:44,640 --> 00:21:47,040
At the gathering I told
you I'd have no part

249
00:21:47,080 --> 00:21:49,880
of these laws that you
intend to force upon the tribes.

250
00:21:49,920 --> 00:21:55,760
Then your people arrive at
Banning. Uninvited, without warning,

251
00:21:55,800 --> 00:21:59,040
and erect a giant log outside
of my hall, Rheda!

252
00:21:59,080 --> 00:22:03,400
Covered in the same wretched
laws that I quite clearly...

253
00:22:03,440 --> 00:22:06,360
Lagathorn. Breathe.

254
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:08,713
You're going red.

255
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:15,960
Well, go on. I take
it you haven't finished.

256
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:19,880
A log, accompanied
by a message from you,

257
00:22:19,920 --> 00:22:26,080
insisting that I publicly
declare that these laws will be upheld

258
00:22:26,120 --> 00:22:28,120
by the Banning.

259
00:22:28,160 --> 00:22:29,960
And?

260
00:22:33,920 --> 00:22:35,920
Why, Rheda?

261
00:22:35,960 --> 00:22:37,960
Please tell me.

262
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:40,000
What is the point in these laws?

263
00:22:41,160 --> 00:22:44,400
I'll do better. I'll show you.

264
00:22:45,360 --> 00:22:48,266
(SNARLING)

265
00:22:57,080 --> 00:22:59,080
- Where's Razzak?
- He's gone.

266
00:22:59,120 --> 00:23:01,240
Slipped away while we were busy here.

267
00:23:01,280 --> 00:23:03,724
- (ROARS)
- These rags.

268
00:23:04,720 --> 00:23:06,720
These are the Haji warband.

269
00:23:06,760 --> 00:23:08,760
They live in the woods near Banning.

270
00:23:09,960 --> 00:23:12,080
What are you doing here, you ugly runt?

271
00:23:12,120 --> 00:23:15,760
Huh? Why aren't you scared?

272
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:17,591
(GROWLS)

273
00:23:17,840 --> 00:23:19,840
Did you learn anything from it?

274
00:23:21,960 --> 00:23:23,960
Only that it has no fear.

275
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:25,220
(GROWLS)

276
00:23:30,240 --> 00:23:31,777
Kill it.

277
00:23:44,760 --> 00:23:46,599
(SNARLING)

278
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:49,749
(TALKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

279
00:24:03,040 --> 00:24:04,608
(SHRIEKS)

280
00:24:08,560 --> 00:24:11,149
If you want a fight, let me out of here!

281
00:24:13,040 --> 00:24:15,769
(SNARLS AND ROARS)

282
00:24:24,960 --> 00:24:26,340
(ROARS)

283
00:24:33,760 --> 00:24:36,040
- Leave him.
- (REPLIES IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

284
00:24:39,640 --> 00:24:40,920
(SCREECHES)

285
00:24:43,520 --> 00:24:45,520
(YELLS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

286
00:24:47,960 --> 00:24:49,960
No more.

287
00:24:55,480 --> 00:24:58,321
You! Get us out of here!

288
00:25:02,560 --> 00:25:06,120
- (SNARLING)
- Where did these people come from?

289
00:25:06,160 --> 00:25:08,000
Who are they?

290
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:16,000
You know the Warig tongue?

291
00:25:21,040 --> 00:25:23,040
Lower her cage.

292
00:25:23,080 --> 00:25:25,080
Who are you?

293
00:25:30,720 --> 00:25:33,040
If you harm her, I will hunt you down!

294
00:25:43,080 --> 00:25:45,520
Why have you been feeding the beast?

295
00:25:49,480 --> 00:25:53,440
You put yourself in more
danger by your silence.

296
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:58,600
Here. Which do you care for most?

297
00:26:03,080 --> 00:26:05,600
The Red Blood or the beast?

298
00:26:09,320 --> 00:26:13,440
Take the blade. Put
it out of its misery.

299
00:26:13,480 --> 00:26:15,480
And I'll let you and the one go.

300
00:26:15,520 --> 00:26:19,537
Do it, Elvina. Kill it!

301
00:26:21,680 --> 00:26:23,304
Why are you doing this?

302
00:26:23,720 --> 00:26:26,526
To know who you are.

303
00:26:48,720 --> 00:26:51,229
(MUTTERING)

304
00:26:55,040 --> 00:26:56,696
(RAGGED BREATHING)

305
00:27:09,320 --> 00:27:10,927
(CRIES OUT)

306
00:27:12,960 --> 00:27:14,960
- Run!
- (SNARLS)

307
00:27:25,280 --> 00:27:26,673
(YELLING)

308
00:27:28,840 --> 00:27:30,840
- Beowulf, forgive me!
- Elvina!

309
00:27:33,320 --> 00:27:34,587
Let her go.

310
00:27:35,360 --> 00:27:38,040
(SPITS) (SPEAKS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

311
00:27:42,080 --> 00:27:43,555
(CRUSHING)

312
00:27:48,880 --> 00:27:51,047
(CHOKING)

313
00:28:02,040 --> 00:28:08,320
You're a Skinshifter. The
prophet leading the Warig uprising.

314
00:28:11,600 --> 00:28:13,600
And you, you are Beowulf.

315
00:28:13,640 --> 00:28:15,760
Burner of Warig burial grounds.

316
00:28:15,800 --> 00:28:17,680
It is good that you love death

317
00:28:17,720 --> 00:28:20,200
because you will have the
time to savour your own.

318
00:28:31,600 --> 00:28:33,600
LAGATHORN: So the
Warig are on the warpath.

319
00:28:33,640 --> 00:28:37,000
What does that have to do with the
laws that set out the price of iron

320
00:28:37,040 --> 00:28:39,240
or give you the right to tax my people?

321
00:28:39,280 --> 00:28:41,760
RHEDA: Before there was a
law setting the price of iron

322
00:28:41,800 --> 00:28:44,480
the miners were threatening
to sell their ore elsewhere.

323
00:28:44,520 --> 00:28:48,240
And with the taxes raised,
we can build bridges, roads,

324
00:28:48,280 --> 00:28:50,280
easing trade and our defence.

325
00:28:52,280 --> 00:28:55,440
These laws bind us
together. They make us stronger.

326
00:28:56,440 --> 00:28:58,440
We owe this to our people.

327
00:29:07,760 --> 00:29:12,960
Our cloaks are red for the blood
we would spill to protect Herot

328
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:15,000
as our brother here did.

329
00:29:15,040 --> 00:29:18,440
- Remember him.
- ALL: We remember.

330
00:29:21,040 --> 00:29:23,040
Who will take up our brother's spear?

331
00:29:23,080 --> 00:29:24,298
I will.

332
00:29:32,600 --> 00:29:34,560
Who will take up our brother's blade?

333
00:29:34,600 --> 00:29:36,009
I will.

334
00:29:38,840 --> 00:29:40,083
I will.

335
00:29:49,000 --> 00:29:50,880
What's the problem between you and Gil?

336
00:29:50,920 --> 00:29:52,920
Gil?

337
00:29:54,520 --> 00:29:56,520
I think he's wrong.

338
00:29:57,600 --> 00:30:00,480
We, as Huskarla, should be
training the people to bear arms,

339
00:30:00,520 --> 00:30:02,520
to use real swords.

340
00:30:02,560 --> 00:30:05,680
If you want your brothers to
stand shoulder-to-shoulder with you

341
00:30:05,720 --> 00:30:08,280
on the battlefield, you
must stand with them off it.

342
00:30:08,320 --> 00:30:10,840
Your duty is to do as he asks.

343
00:30:10,880 --> 00:30:12,880
Gil, come here.

344
00:30:15,240 --> 00:30:17,240
I give you an order to train the people.

345
00:30:18,720 --> 00:30:20,720
Brinni, go with him.

346
00:30:26,920 --> 00:30:28,642
(GRUNTING)

347
00:30:34,480 --> 00:30:36,139
(SNARLING)

348
00:30:42,040 --> 00:30:43,158
Lila.

349
00:30:45,240 --> 00:30:48,160
You speak for the people on
this matter of the Huskarla training?

350
00:30:48,200 --> 00:30:49,960
- I do.
- When do we start?

351
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:52,000
- We don't.
- Why?

352
00:30:52,040 --> 00:30:55,240
You fight with your
axes and knives. Not swords.

353
00:30:55,280 --> 00:30:57,760
None of you can stand against
the likes of us in battle.

354
00:30:57,800 --> 00:30:59,378
- Even with training.
- Your father's

355
00:30:59,521 --> 00:31:02,280
ancestors weren't born Huskarla.

356
00:31:02,320 --> 00:31:05,360
They earned the right to wear the
red cloak and sit at the high table

357
00:31:05,400 --> 00:31:07,400
by their bravery.

358
00:31:07,440 --> 00:31:08,880
We're done.

359
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:12,760
Then we will refuse
to forge your swords.

360
00:31:15,080 --> 00:31:17,680
- Really?
- I have to prioritise the work.

361
00:31:17,720 --> 00:31:19,061
(CHUCKLES)

362
00:31:19,760 --> 00:31:22,400
Fine. Then we'll fix them ourselves.

363
00:31:22,440 --> 00:31:24,800
I ever tell you I worked in a tavern?

364
00:31:24,840 --> 00:31:26,840
Lila... (GROANS)

365
00:31:26,880 --> 00:31:27,998
(COUGHS)

366
00:31:28,920 --> 00:31:32,560
None of us could stand
against the likes of you in battle?

367
00:31:32,600 --> 00:31:37,520
Give me five good barmaids, I
could take an army of Huskarla.

368
00:31:37,560 --> 00:31:39,560
Well?

369
00:31:39,600 --> 00:31:43,000
Are you the kind that gets
bitter or the kind that gets on?

370
00:31:48,720 --> 00:31:51,000
(SIGHS) Bring your
people to the arena tomorrow.

371
00:31:51,040 --> 00:31:52,349
We'll see what they're made of.

372
00:31:53,080 --> 00:31:55,360
The more barmaids the better, hm?

373
00:32:20,400 --> 00:32:22,439
(GROWLING)

374
00:32:40,480 --> 00:32:42,920
The Defiler. For you, Kragen.

375
00:32:46,840 --> 00:32:50,720
I'd welcome your help to drive
the Red Bloods from these lands.

376
00:32:53,173 --> 00:32:55,480
I have seen Herot. It is weak.

377
00:33:12,440 --> 00:33:13,599
(GROWLS)

378
00:33:18,200 --> 00:33:20,200
He wants to know if you
have anything to say.

379
00:33:21,640 --> 00:33:23,520
Only that if he breathes
on me any longer,

380
00:33:23,560 --> 00:33:25,560
he won't have any use for that spear.

381
00:33:25,600 --> 00:33:26,905
(CRIES OUT)

382
00:33:27,640 --> 00:33:29,439
He understands.

383
00:33:30,240 --> 00:33:31,687
Yeah, I got that.

384
00:33:37,760 --> 00:33:39,713
Argh!

385
00:33:39,800 --> 00:33:42,920
He says you'll burn, as
you burned their dead priest

386
00:33:42,960 --> 00:33:46,360
and robbed this ground of
all meaning as a holy place.

387
00:33:56,080 --> 00:33:58,320
Say for a moment I buy
what you're selling.

388
00:33:58,360 --> 00:34:00,720
This risk of a Warig uprising...

389
00:34:00,760 --> 00:34:03,800
The Varni are banished,
the Mere are ghost people

390
00:34:03,840 --> 00:34:08,199
and the rest are farmers. I have
to know I can rely on your support.

391
00:34:08,239 --> 00:34:13,480
Should Herot come under threat we
need your archers. Your woodmen.

392
00:34:17,960 --> 00:34:19,639
(HORSE WHINNIES)

393
00:34:19,679 --> 00:34:24,120
You have my word. I'll send my
warriors should Herot need them.

394
00:34:25,920 --> 00:34:28,719
See, I still have the capacity
to surprise you don't I, Rheda?

395
00:34:28,760 --> 00:34:30,760
Always.

396
00:34:33,239 --> 00:34:35,320
Now you're waiting
for the sting in the tail.

397
00:34:35,360 --> 00:34:37,360
And you won't disappoint me.

398
00:34:37,400 --> 00:34:40,280
I have your word? If...

399
00:34:40,320 --> 00:34:43,560
If I don't have to take the laws.

400
00:34:47,719 --> 00:34:49,156
Take down your banner.

401
00:34:49,760 --> 00:34:52,853
The Banning many have their own laws.

402
00:34:55,320 --> 00:34:56,599
I'll drink to that.

403
00:35:00,080 --> 00:35:02,080
I can always have another one made.

404
00:35:02,120 --> 00:35:04,728
When the time is right.

405
00:35:05,640 --> 00:35:08,179
(CHUCKLES)

406
00:35:09,880 --> 00:35:11,880
(LAUGHS)

407
00:35:13,680 --> 00:35:16,844
(SNARLING)

408
00:35:21,600 --> 00:35:25,059
(SPEAKS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

409
00:35:48,760 --> 00:35:51,250
No! No!

410
00:35:53,440 --> 00:35:55,522
(YELLS)

411
00:35:56,680 --> 00:35:58,355
No!

412
00:35:58,720 --> 00:36:00,960
No! (CRIES OUT)

413
00:36:08,200 --> 00:36:10,200
Beowulf!

414
00:36:11,640 --> 00:36:13,640
(ROARS)

415
00:36:16,400 --> 00:36:18,147
(SCREECHES)

416
00:36:21,760 --> 00:36:23,620
(YELLS)

417
00:36:55,520 --> 00:36:56,708
Run!

418
00:37:06,840 --> 00:37:08,840
(HISSES)

419
00:37:08,880 --> 00:37:10,880
(MUTTERING AND YELLING)

420
00:37:20,760 --> 00:37:22,760
(PANTING)

421
00:37:22,800 --> 00:37:24,800
(SNARLING)

422
00:37:34,400 --> 00:37:36,174
(YELLS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

423
00:37:53,440 --> 00:37:54,527
(CHOKING CRY)

424
00:37:55,480 --> 00:37:58,400
I am Razzak, son of
Kathal, last of my line.

425
00:37:58,440 --> 00:38:01,680
- (GROANS)
- I am your saviour.

426
00:38:13,680 --> 00:38:15,680
(SCREECHES)

427
00:38:15,720 --> 00:38:17,720
(SCREECHING ECHOES)

428
00:39:02,840 --> 00:39:04,840
(SPEAKS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

429
00:39:08,880 --> 00:39:10,880
See what the Defiler has done.

430
00:39:10,920 --> 00:39:13,400
Beowulf has murdered your leader.

431
00:39:13,440 --> 00:39:15,440
Kragen must be avenged.

432
00:39:15,480 --> 00:39:18,280
- (MURMURING)
- We need to save this land.

433
00:39:18,320 --> 00:39:21,560
Save it from the humans...

434
00:39:21,600 --> 00:39:24,680
who butchered your fathers and mothers.

435
00:39:24,720 --> 00:39:27,640
And they will butcher their children.

436
00:39:29,080 --> 00:39:31,200
That's why we'll defeat them!

437
00:39:31,240 --> 00:39:35,120
I am your prophet and
together, we the Mudborn,

438
00:39:35,160 --> 00:39:37,150
will drive them from our lands!

439
00:39:37,200 --> 00:39:40,320
- (SNARLING AND YELLING)
- And take back what is ours!

440
00:39:40,360 --> 00:39:41,803
(CHEERING)

441
00:39:42,400 --> 00:39:46,920
We are not ashamed of this dark
earth that gave us life.

442
00:39:47,920 --> 00:39:50,640
For the honour of
those who came before us.

443
00:39:50,680 --> 00:39:54,440
For the future of those who follow!

444
00:39:54,480 --> 00:39:55,827
(CHEERING)

445
00:40:07,320 --> 00:40:08,747
(GASPS)

446
00:40:14,960 --> 00:40:16,495
What are you?

447
00:40:44,920 --> 00:40:46,938
Never come back to Herot.

448
00:40:48,680 --> 00:40:49,916
You're dead to them.

449
00:40:55,680 --> 00:40:57,337
You're dead to me.

450
00:41:12,160 --> 00:41:13,767
(ANIMAL HOWLS)

451
00:42:07,040 --> 00:42:10,125
(CLANGING AND VOICES IN DISTANCE)

452
00:42:12,120 --> 00:42:13,152
Stay here.

453
00:42:26,560 --> 00:42:29,800
You saw this Warig
prophet? This Skinshifter?

454
00:42:29,840 --> 00:42:31,164
Razzak.

455
00:42:31,880 --> 00:42:34,160
I was as close to him as I am to you.

456
00:42:34,200 --> 00:42:36,200
He was here.

457
00:42:36,240 --> 00:42:37,543
Why?

458
00:42:38,280 --> 00:42:42,000
To know our weaknesses before he tries
to force us from these lands.

459
00:42:44,640 --> 00:42:45,927
Was Elvina with you?

460
00:42:53,560 --> 00:42:54,702
Where is she?

461
00:42:59,920 --> 00:43:02,314
- Elvina's dead.
- (GASPS)

462
00:43:12,400 --> 00:43:14,196
How?

463
00:43:16,520 --> 00:43:17,537
Warig.

464
00:43:23,240 --> 00:43:25,091
The people are scared enough.

465
00:43:27,600 --> 00:43:30,280
We tell no-one of this. Yet.

466
00:43:59,560 --> 00:44:01,560
Breca...

467
00:44:05,040 --> 00:44:10,240
Just a precaution. I don't want
you killing me for coming back.

468
00:44:11,720 --> 00:44:13,170
Put it down or I will.

469
00:44:19,320 --> 00:44:20,704
I've had a bad day.

470
00:44:23,240 --> 00:44:25,240
It's going to get worse.

471
00:44:25,280 --> 00:44:28,280
Abrecan is going to attack Herot.

472
00:44:34,960 --> 00:44:36,600
Abrecan would never betray me.

473
00:44:36,640 --> 00:44:39,600
I heard him call for his
people to attack Herot.

474
00:44:39,640 --> 00:44:41,640
Prepare to fight our real enemy.

475
00:44:42,960 --> 00:44:45,280
You are all here to learn
to fight like Huskarla.

476
00:44:46,200 --> 00:44:48,880
Rheda, you're riding straight
into the arms of your enemy.

477
00:44:48,920 --> 00:44:50,720
I've been hearing things. About you.

478
00:44:50,760 --> 00:44:53,240
- Rumours.
- Run.

479
00:44:55,480 --> 00:44:57,323
- (ROARING)
- It's killed a human.

480
00:44:57,348 --> 00:44:58,920
We have to hunt it down.

481
00:44:58,960 --> 00:45:01,680
- Let's take it back.
- (ROARING)

482
00:45:02,680 --> 00:45:04,680
Beowulf! He's going to kill it!

483
00:45:04,720 --> 00:45:05,855
(YELLS)

